# Community tone of voice

When writing, editing, or rewriting any user-facing text for percona.community — markdown content, frontmatter (`title`, `description`, etc.), page copy, CTAs, event announcements, blog posts, newsletters, and social captions — read and follow:

`.cursor/skills/community-tone-of-voice-writer/SKILL.md`

Before writing, read the relevant reference files in that skill when needed:

- `references/content-formats.md` — format rules by content type
- `references/voice-examples.md` — tone examples
- `references/editorial-style-guide.md` — naming, punctuation, grammar

This is community content, not marketing copy. Write like an engineer talking to another engineer. Do not use marketing or sales voice.
